1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,721
A special word of caution.

2
00:00:00,831 --> 00:00:03,520
Be careful about your source of advice.

3
00:00:03,791 --> 00:00:12,081
In most organizations you will encounter freelance advisors who know the ropes and are tremendously eager to clue you in.

4
00:00:12,431 --> 00:00:20,240
One time I overheard a freelance advisor explaining the facts of office life to a bright young man just starting in.

5
00:00:20,591 --> 00:00:22,000
said the advisor.

6
00:00:22,191 --> 00:00:26,560
The best way to get along here is just stay out of everybody's way.

7
00:00:26,671 --> 00:00:30,961
If they ever get to know you, all they'll do is pile more work on you.

8
00:00:31,230 --> 00:00:36,240
Be especially careful to stay away from Mr. Z, the department manager.

9
00:00:36,351 --> 00:00:40,721
If he thinks you haven't got enough to do, he'll really load you down.

10
00:00:41,391 --> 00:00:48,721
This freelance advisor had been with the company for almost 30 years and was still bottom man on the totem pole.

11
00:00:48,990 --> 00:00:55,040
What a consultant for a young man who wants to move upward in the business.

12
00:00:55,151 --> 00:00:59,121
Make it a rule to seek advice from people who know.

13
00:00:59,951 --> 00:01:04,881
There's a lot of incorrect thinking that successful people are inaccessible.

14
00:01:04,990 --> 00:01:07,361
The plain truth is that they are not.

15
00:01:07,711 --> 00:01:13,121
As a rule, it's the more successful people who are the most humble and ready to help.

16
00:01:13,471 --> 00:01:23,760
Since they are sincerely interested in their work and success, they are eager to see that the work lives on and that somebody capable succeeds them when they retire.

17
00:01:24,031 --> 00:01:30,240
It's the would-be big people who are most often the most abrupt and hard to get to know.

18
00:01:31,071 --> 00:01:33,280
An executive made this clear.

19
00:01:33,631 --> 00:01:38,560
I'm a busy woman, but there's no Do Not Disturb sign on my office door.

20
00:01:38,831 --> 00:01:41,760
Counseling people is one of my key functions.

21
00:01:42,031 --> 00:01:46,881
We give standardized training of one kind or another to everybody in the company.

22
00:01:47,071 --> 00:01:52,800
But personal counseling or tutoring, as I like to call it, is available for the asking.

23
00:01:53,391 --> 00:01:59,361
I stand ready to help the fellow who comes in here with either a company or a personal problem.

24
00:01:59,711 --> 00:02:10,401
The fellow who displays curiosity and exhibits a real desire to know more about his job and how it relates to other jobs is the individual I like most to help.

25
00:02:10,990 --> 00:02:19,280
But, she said, for obvious reasons, I can't spend time offering advice to anybody who isn't sincere in seeking it.

26
00:02:19,951 --> 00:02:22,800
Go first class when you have questions.

27
00:02:22,990 --> 00:02:28,800
Seeking advice from a failure is like consulting a quack on how to cure cancer.

28
00:02:30,591 --> 00:02:37,681
Many executives today never employ persons for key jobs without first interviewing the fellow's wife.

29
00:02:38,351 --> 00:02:45,280
One sales executive explained to me, I want to be sure the prospective salesman has his family behind him,
